                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 18643/13.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Dudley</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Petropolis</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-01-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 16, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Ambassador Dudley reports that Brazil has granted to the United States a
                    differential tariff reduction of 20 per cent during 1910 on 11 articles which
                    were so favored in 1909, and which will be construed to include alarm clocks,
                    and in addition cement, desks, dried fruit, school furniture, and corsets.</p>
            </div>
